===Product Overview=== <small> *[[Acelink EW-7956MAC]] 802.11ac 5GHz Solution: :Acelink EW-7956MAC is an 802.11ac/a/n 5GHz Single-Band Mini PCI express module :based on [[Qualcomm Atheros]] QCA9994 chipset and [[Skyworks]] power amplifier. :It supports 4T4R (4x4) technology, which runs up to 1.73Gbps (11ac VHT80 MCS9). :EW-7956MAC supports 20/40/80MHz and 256-QAM to maximize bandwidth efficiency. :EW-7956MAC supports 4.9GHz with narrow band application by HT5 / HT10 / HT20. *Secure Wireless Connection :Incorporated with advanced security encryption, such as 64/128-bits WEP, WPA, :WPA2, and 802.1x, it helps prevent usersâ€™ devices from malicious attacks. </small> ===Specifications=== *Host Interface: Mini PCIe *Standard: 802.11a/n/ac *Chipset: Qualcomm Atheros QCA9994 *Amplifiers: 4x 5GHz High Power Amp SKY85405 *Operating Frequency: :ISM band: 5.150~5.825GHz :4.9GHz (HT5/HT10/HT20) *Operation Channels: :5GHz : Country dependent for the following ranges: :36, 40, 44, 48, 52, 56, 60, 64, 100, 104, 108, 112, 116, :120, 124, 128, 132, 136, 140, 149, 153, 157, 161, 165 *Data Rates: 802.11a: 6-54Mbps :802.11n: MCS0~MCS31 :802.11ac: VHT80 MCS0~MCS9 *Antenna Connectors: 4x iPEX :Connectors reserved for 5GHz antenna *Operating Voltage: DC 5V *Power Consumption: 9.5W *Dimensions: 48mm x 73mm
